Eli Lilly and Company, known for its diverse portfolio of pharmaceutical offerings, including arthritis medications, is a notable player in the global arthritis**Global Arthritis Market Analysis:**

- **Rheumatoid Drug Type:** The global arthritis market, by rheumatoid drug type, includes biologics, non-biologics, steroids, analgesics, glucocorticoids, and others. Biologics have gained significant traction in the market due to their targeted approach in treating rheumatoid arthritis by inhibiting specific components of the immune system. Non-biologics and steroids are also commonly prescribed for managing inflammation and pain associated with arthritis, while analgesics play a crucial role in pain management.

- **Rheumatoid Treatment:** In terms of rheumatoid treatment, options such as synovectomy, tendon repair, joint fusion, symptomatic treatment, intermediate corticosteroid therapies, and Disease Modifying Anti-Rheumatic Drugs (DMARDs) are available in the market. These treatments aim to alleviate symptoms, slow down disease progression, and improve the quality of life for arthritis patients. DMARDs, in particular, have shown efficacy in modifying the course of rheumatoid arthritis by targeting the underlying immune dysfunction.

- **Rheumatoid Diagnosis:** The diagnosis of rheumatoid arthritis involves tests such as C-reactive protein (C.R.P.) test, cyclic citrullinated peptide (C.C.P.) test, and erythrocyte sedimentation rate (E.S.R.) test. These diagnostic tests help healthcare providers confirm the presence of rheumatoid arthritis, assess disease

 

